CASTING CALL - ASAP

25/01/25

The Party No One Wanted (Short Film)

**A dark comedy about grief and family relationships.**

Robbie and Mary have to get through an excruciating memorial that has a DJ, karaoke and a pregnancy announcement / gender reveal planned by their half sister Lisa.

* **Shooting 6th - 9th March in TW19**
* Auditions in Elephant and Castle within the next few weeks
* **Travel Expenses Paid**
* Student film hoping to go to Film festivals
* **Robbie **(28-38yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Emotionally withdrawn but has a kind heart, he's holding it together for Mary and his Dad
* **Steve** (57-70yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Mary, Robbie and Lisa‚Äôs dad doesn‚Äôt get involved in the arguing he‚Äôs still devastated by the loss of his wife but insists he‚Äôs fine.
* **Lisa** (39-47yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Self centred and definitely doesn‚Äôt know whats appropriate at a memorial. 
* **Natalie** (49-65yrs)
   * A close family friend who has taken on a bit of a motherly role to everyone, kind and soft spoken.
* **Bill** (50-65yrs) 
   * The drunk best friend of steve who has awful timing for his awkward comments. Very funny character

**Character Bios: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing)** **

**Director‚Äôs Statement: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing) 

Email: [mhmollie0303@icloud.com](mailto:mhmollie0303@icloud.com) for further details

CASTING CALL ‚Äì LIVERPOOL PERFORMERS WANTED üé≠üé∂

We're casting for "This Girl ‚Äì The Cynthia Lennon Story" ‚Äì a sell-out original musical returning to the stage at Capstone Theatre, Liverpool in May 2026.

We always talk about him. This time, the spotlight is on her.

This powerful musical tells the story of Cynthia Lennon and how she met John ‚Äì featuring all original songs, including 'Mother Mary' by Julian Lennon. Previously performed to packed houses in Liverpool and London.

Roles available:
üé∏ Stuart Sutcliffe ‚Äì singer & guitarist, male, playing age 18-25
üé§ Musical theatre singers & dancers ‚Äì male/female, 6-8 roles
üé¨ Aunt Mimi ‚Äì female, playing age 40+

Key dates:
üìÖ Auditions: Early February
üìÖ Rehearsals: April onwards @ Hope Street University
üìÖ Performances: 29th & 30th May 2026
üìç Venue: Capstone Theatre, Liverpool

This is a paid role (profit share)

This is a unique opportunity to be part of a critically acclaimed production celebrating a Liverpool icon whose story deserves to be told.

To apply: Send your CV and headshot to howl.michael1963@yahoo.co.uk

Aunt Mimi - Please prepare a 2-minute monologue of your choice for audition.
Stuart Sutcliffe - please prepare a short monologue and a song which you will sing accompanying yourself with the guitar
Musical Theatre Students: Please prepare a number of your choice which includes singing and dancing

#CastingCall #LiverpoolActors #MusicalTheatre #TheatreJobs #Liverpool #CynthiaLennon #ActorsWanted #NorthWestTheatre #SingersWanted #DancersWanted

29-31 January in Berlin.

In this workshop Antonia Cezara CioazƒÉ and Jakob Nielsen are sharing their personal training called IMAGINING WITH THE BODY-MIND which they have developed together with their director, Eugenio Barba since January 2022. 

The training is based on the use of imagination in the pre-expressive level of the creative process of the actor.

Through guided work in embodied presence and spontaneous exploration, participants learn to access their intuitive responses and channel them into focused, expressive action. The participants will explore composition by practising varied ways of walking and dancing. 

They can use the exercises in their personal practice order to enhance their stage presence. The exercises are crafted to let participants tap into their own associations, opening pathways to authentic expression on stage.

More details: [https://imaginingbodymind.carrd.co](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimaginingbodymind.carrd.co%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQQMjIyMDM5MTc4ODIwMDg5MgABHmwgV6ATObZ3kmmCDbESsuL7JJ8ikSuIXxovuJRvRolTYi2wK_hX9m28KHjI_aem_KXbemAkoiwLRQWeL6zJhhA&h=AT1H9OBzjQyXL6cmaONDfv0q223N8TRU6_uKZ4Av-zAritd4t408rQzHkwAUTZW17V52l6-dScMAYaAK3IADk0mHta98eae8pHcZF6NotDXMduXrRRMtM6A-fjhv27QqroYSnuopKrBSfoLQC88NnWZuHHptDA&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT3Lu1X4iM3PjxlrZwntZon8UXjvDj_OF40QYKaLurcg3zTswjbkbQ0I37wr9A_DnWB-dMmSp7Gjfv2bdzW3Hz4xBdeGCsrCaS_q8-vhY0wx-LZJ9XPS6WW6h5LFRkzxkA_7KEqO49p2eU6mrqpY3XF0Tzidw2rwKLC-HsjMOmsQYyYryoA2JDveMds)

29-31 January in Berlin.

In this workshop Antonia Cezara CioazƒÉ and Jakob Nielsen are sharing their personal training called IMAGINING WITH THE BODY-MIND which they have developed together with their director, Eugenio Barba since January 2022. 

The training is based on the use of imagination in the pre-expressive level of the creative process of the actor.

Through guided work in embodied presence and spontaneous exploration, participants learn to access their intuitive responses and channel them into focused, expressive action. The participants will explore composition by practising varied ways of walking and dancing. 

They can use the exercises in their personal practice order to enhance their stage presence. The exercises are crafted to let participants tap into their own associations, opening pathways to authentic expression on stage.

More details: [https://imaginingbodymind.carrd.co](https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimaginingbodymind.carrd.co%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAc3J0YwZhcHBfaWQQMjIyMDM5MTc4ODIwMDg5MgABHmwgV6ATObZ3kmmCDbESsuL7JJ8ikSuIXxovuJRvRolTYi2wK_hX9m28KHjI_aem_KXbemAkoiwLRQWeL6zJhhA&h=AT1H9OBzjQyXL6cmaONDfv0q223N8TRU6_uKZ4Av-zAritd4t408rQzHkwAUTZW17V52l6-dScMAYaAK3IADk0mHta98eae8pHcZF6NotDXMduXrRRMtM6A-fjhv27QqroYSnuopKrBSfoLQC88NnWZuHHptDA&__tn__=-UK-R&c[0]=AT3Lu1X4iM3PjxlrZwntZon8UXjvDj_OF40QYKaLurcg3zTswjbkbQ0I37wr9A_DnWB-dMmSp7Gjfv2bdzW3Hz4xBdeGCsrCaS_q8-vhY0wx-LZJ9XPS6WW6h5LFRkzxkA_7KEqO49p2eU6mrqpY3XF0Tzidw2rwKLC-HsjMOmsQYyYryoA2JDveMds)

We are now casting our Spring show Shake Rattle And Roll and looking for self Contained experienced hardworking performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community .The
The show is a celebration to all the greatest songs and stars of the 50s 60s 70s The Beatles ,Elvis, Doris Day, Connie Francis ,Cliff Richard, Buddy Holly and more.

Dates

Rehearsals- 23rd -27th February 

Playing Dates- 2nd March-3rd May 

We work Monday to Friday (2 x 60 minute shows per day) 

Casting Breakdown We are now looking for strong /experienced Male and Female singer /performers 

The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced performers that can hold an audience and are looking for engaging vocalist performers.

We are looking for drivers with cars only .

We are looking for performers on all area of the UK -please include bases when sending details.

We are offering 700 per week plus fuel on the road 

Please send details including a singing reel to info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

CASTING CALL
On the way to their final gig, four childhood bestfriends in a girl band take a roadside detour that forces them to confront the truth about moving on and unresolved tensions.

Genre: Comedy/ Coming-of-age

Looking for 3 Females aged 18-22 for a Falmouth University Graduation Film!! 

- Rita 

- Callie

- Gracie

 Able to play the instruments desirable but NOT needed!!! 

Rates + Travel/Food covered

Shoot dates: 4th March - 12th March + rehearsals beforehand. 

If interested, please email glittergrungefilm@gmail.com with a self tape or showreel!! We will send our script for a self tape! 

CORNWALL BASED ONLY

More info on our instagram @glittergrungefilm

We can't wait to hear from you!!

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

Casting call - Stray Dog
Currently casting all roles for 10 minute graduate film based in Bristol and surrounding areas. 

Set in the 1930‚Äôs, Stray Dog follows two silent cinema owning brothers during the rise of the ‚ÄúTalkies‚Äù. Oz leaves his brother and sets up his travelling cinema with lover Nancy. They party and discover how it feels to be free, but grow apart when Oz can‚Äôt learn to be serious. Eventually, a car crash allows Oz to come to terms with who he‚Äôs become and reflect on the important things in life. 

As it‚Äôs a student film, we are seeking contributors on a voluntary basis, but food and travel expenses will be covered. 

Shoot length is a maximum of 5 days, and will take place between end of February and start of March (dates TBC). 

We would love to hear from you! Please email: ttpsfilm@yahoo.com

items.summary:
Casting call - Stray Dog
Currently casting all roles for 10 minute graduate film based in Bristol and surrounding areas. 

Set in the 1930‚Äôs, Stray Dog follows two silent cinema owning brothers during the rise of the ‚ÄúTalkies‚Äù. Oz leaves his brother and sets up his travelling cinema with lover Nancy. They party and discover how it feels to be free, but grow apart when Oz can‚Äôt learn to be serious. Eventually, a car crash allows Oz to come to terms with who he‚Äôs become and reflect on the important things in life. 

As it‚Äôs a student film, we are seeking contributors on a voluntary basis, but food and travel expenses will be covered. 

Shoot length is a maximum of 5 days, and will take place between end of February and start of March (dates TBC). 

We would love to hear from you! Please email: ttpsfilm@yahoo.com

Comedy short film - 10 minutes 

A struggling theater show is made worse by a new member of the crew who‚Äôs inexperience makes it a night to remember.

Lee (male 20-30)

An ambitious theatre worker who is always wanting more out of life. Can be naive to the ways of the world but has blind optimism that gets him

through stressful times.

George (male 20-30)

A sarcastic, hardworking tech worker who struggles to find joy from his work. Wants to use his talents elsewhere but has no motivation to do so.

Jamie (female 25-35)

The theatre plays stressed out director who struggles with the demand of the actors and lack of backstage crew.

Expenses paid only

Location: Aylesbury 

If interested contact: ruth.merry@outlook.com

items.text:
üé•CASTING CALL ‚Äî WAR-TIME DRAMA SHORT FILM

We are casting Enemy Soldiers and Civilians for an intense, large-scale Field Hospital sequence in a war-time drama short film.

üìÖ January 24‚Äì25 (primarily Sunday, January 25)
üìç Big Dalton, Glendora

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

items.text:
CASTING CALL - ASAP

25/01/25

The Party No One Wanted (Short Film)

**A dark comedy about grief and family relationships.**

Robbie and Mary have to get through an excruciating memorial that has a DJ, karaoke and a pregnancy announcement / gender reveal planned by their half sister Lisa.

* **Shooting 6th - 9th March in TW19**
* Auditions in Elephant and Castle within the next few weeks
* **Travel Expenses Paid**
* Student film hoping to go to Film festivals
* **Robbie **(28-38yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Emotionally withdrawn but has a kind heart, he's holding it together for Mary and his Dad
* **Steve** (57-70yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Mary, Robbie and Lisa‚Äôs dad doesn‚Äôt get involved in the arguing he‚Äôs still devastated by the loss of his wife but insists he‚Äôs fine.
* **Lisa** (39-47yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Self centred and definitely doesn‚Äôt know whats appropriate at a memorial. 
* **Natalie** (49-65yrs)
   * A close family friend who has taken on a bit of a motherly role to everyone, kind and soft spoken.
* **Bill** (50-65yrs) 
   * The drunk best friend of steve who has awful timing for his awkward comments. Very funny character

**Character Bios: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing)** **

**Director‚Äôs Statement: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing) 

Email: [mhmollie0303@icloud.com](mailto:mhmollie0303@icloud.com) for further details

items.text:
Reminder. Audition Monday coming. 26th. Wanted: 2 actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays.

We are looking for two versatile actors for our Leverhulme Drama Festival plays: ‚ÄúThe Balled of Crooked Lane‚Äù by Tom Mclennan and ‚ÄúWake‚Äù by Day Sheehan, to be performed on Wed 25th February (the awards evening) at the Gladstone Theatre, Port Sunlight. Both play were part of the Liverpool Fringe and won numerous nominations for best play etc.

Plays and parts descriptions.
‚ÄúThe Ballad of Crooked Lane‚Äù is set on the day Edward Rushton, prominent anti-slavery campaigner and blind poet, now well into middle age, awaits eye surgery to regain his sight. While waiting, he goes over his eventful life with his friend and biographer, William Shepherd, the Minister of Gateacre Chapel.

The part: The actor would play Billy the Ballad-monger in one important scene, a lively, upfront character full of humour, a seller of broadside ballads and casual acquaintance of Rushton. The actor would also fulfil several other small roles and be fully active on stage in what is an ensemble production.

‚ÄúWake‚Äù When Daniel Anderson finds himself in an unfamiliar place with fragments of the previous night missing from his memory, he must piece together the truth of what happened. This experimental drama explores themes of guilt, responsibility, and the price of self-deception in a world where nothing is quite what it seems.

The part: POLICE OFFICER 2 (Any gender, 30s+) - The psychological manipulator who probes emotional wounds. The actor needs to be versatile as this role requires them to be multi faceted

No particular age or even gender is necessarily required We are looking for  actors who can bring the characters to life.

Audition date: Monday 26th January 7pm. Valley Theatre, Childwall Valley Rd, Liverpool L27 3YA

Contact info@valleytheatre.co.uk or turn up on the night. No prep needed. audition will consist of short extract from the script.

Please note: There is no fee for these roles. Hopefully the material and occasion will appeal.

Hoping to shoot in summer 2026, dependent on funding. I‚Äôm looking to fill the remaining three roles for the gang of four lads that are essentially the main focus of the film (besides Cookie, the lead role). These are chief supporting roles, and all roles in the film are paid.

**Marketing Interns: Your Next Big Opportunity is Here! üöÄ**

**Kandid Media** is urgently seeking dynamic and driven **Marketing Interns** to join our fast-paced team for a 60-day intensive program.

This isn't just about fetching coffee‚Äîit's about diving headfirst into real-world media strategy, content creation, and campaign execution. If you're ready to learn, innovate, and make a tangible impact, this is your shot.

**The Pathway:** We believe in rewarding talent and hard work. After a successful 60-day internship, top performers will be invited to transition into a **paid part-time position** with Kandid Media. This is your chance to turn passion into profession.

**We're looking for individuals who are:**
* Eager to learn about media, content strategy, and digital marketing.
* Proactive, creative, and reliable.
* Ready to contribute to a growing media company.

**Why Join Kandid Media?** You'll work alongside experienced professionals, gain invaluable hands-on experience, and contribute to projects that span film, branded content, and community-driven initiatives. This is about building your resume with real results and securing your future in the industry.

**Apply Now: Send us a DM with a brief overview of your marketing interest/experience and what social platforms you have the greatest knowledge in. **

We're moving fast, so don't delay!

items.text:
What‚Äôs the similarity between an aerialist and a fighter pilot? ü§î
Complete control over speed and vector‚ÄºÔ∏è

Engineered for the extreme:
‚úî Speed control 0-1.5 m/s: From weightless hovering to dynamic takeoff, like the acceleration of a fighter jet.
‚úî Emergency brake: Your ejection seat. Instant response to any anomaly. Safety is our priority #1.
‚úî Cable press roller: Our stabilization system. Zero swing, zero jerk. Rail-like trajectory.
‚úî Crane-grade reliability: Industrial-grade components. A safety margin that‚Äôs in a different league.
‚úî Limit switch: The autopilot. Prevents operation beyond safe limits automatically.

This isn‚Äôt just hardware. It‚Äôs a flight engineering system, refined over 11 years.

We know what‚Äôs at stake: not just weight, but an artist‚Äôs destiny, a show‚Äôs reputation, and the audience‚Äôs trust!

Want to give your artists true confidence in the air?
Follow for engineering insights, behind-the-scenes, and technology that redefines aerial performance.

Follow ‚Üí @losinskyi_winches 
Because aerial gymnastics deserves 21st-century technology.
#aerialwinch #aerialgymnastics #circuslife

What‚Äôs the similarity between an aerialist and a fighter pilot? ü§î
Complete control over speed and vector‚ÄºÔ∏è

Engineered for the extreme:
‚úî Speed control 0-1.5 m/s: From weightless hovering to dynamic takeoff, like the acceleration of a fighter jet.
‚úî Emergency brake: Your ejection seat. Instant response to any anomaly. Safety is our priority #1.
‚úî Cable press roller: Our stabilization system. Zero swing, zero jerk. Rail-like trajectory.
‚úî Crane-grade reliability: Industrial-grade components. A safety margin that‚Äôs in a different league.
‚úî Limit switch: The autopilot. Prevents operation beyond safe limits automatically.

This isn‚Äôt just hardware. It‚Äôs a flight engineering system, refined over 11 years.

We know what‚Äôs at stake: not just weight, but an artist‚Äôs destiny, a show‚Äôs reputation, and the audience‚Äôs trust!

Want to give your artists true confidence in the air?
Follow for engineering insights, behind-the-scenes, and technology that redefines aerial performance.

Follow ‚Üí @losinskyi_winches 
Because aerial gymnastics deserves 21st-century technology.
#aerialwinch #aerialgymnastics #circuslife

items.text:
Hello filmmakers! 

One week until our soft deadline! We've received over 50 submissions! Our team has started reading the scripts and narrowing them down. 

If you'd like to submit a script, inquire about being on the crew, acting, or helping produce these projects, send us an email!

These projects will be filmed in the SF Bay Area. Aiming for very low budgets.

Benjaminhorvat.media@gmail.com

Info@TrickyInk.com

(please do NOT add me as a friend or send me a message here. I will not respond)

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'TRICKY INK PRODUCTIONS SEEKING SHORT FILM SCRIPTS Filming 4 shorts this year in Sonoma County, CA ‚Ä¢Under 15 , any genre ¬∑Focus on thought- provoking stories, told by underrepresented communities ‚Ä¢Soft Sof deadline, end of ‚Ä¢Concepts & January WIP also accepted Benjaminhorvat.Media@gmail.com to submit scripts fo@Trickylnk.com for cast/crew/producer inquiries'

topComments.text: Producing four shorts. No film will be used or needed. Film is a specific medium, physical stock, chemical emulsion, lab processing, and mechanical transport through a camera. None of that is present here. What you are making are shorts produced digitally. That is not a downgrade, it is a different technology entirely. Digital video uses sensors, codecs, solid state media, and file based workflows, and it requires a different set of technical and creative skills. Calling a digital production a film describes tools that are not being used and quietly misrepresents the process. Accuracy matters, especially when presenting work professionally. We make movies and not all movies are films, especially in the 21st century.

items.text:
**Actors & Filmmakers Networking Event ‚Äî at HOME Mcr ‚Äî Tickets On Sale Now!**

 

If you‚Äôve been saying, ‚ÄúI need to meet more filmmakers / actors / crew‚Ä¶‚Äù this is your chance. This event is designed to bring Manchester‚Äôs film community into one room‚Äîso come and meet the people who could cast you, crew up with you, create with you, and help bring your next project to life.

After an incredible turnout last October, Christian Le Feuvre & Marble Academy are bringing it back‚Äîbigger, busier, and packed with opportunity for everyone from first-timers to seasoned creatives.

________________________________________

 

**Why you should be in the room**

This isn‚Äôt awkward small talk and business cards that go nowhere. It‚Äôs a welcoming space built for real connections‚Äîthe kind that turn into:

‚úÖ auditions and roles

‚úÖ short films and passion projects

‚úÖ paid gigs and crew calls

‚úÖ creative partnerships that actually last

 

Whether you‚Äôre:

üé≠ an actor looking to get seen by new directors and producers

üé• a director ready to build a reliable team

üìã a producer searching for strong talent and dependable crew

üé¨ crew looking for your next set, your next contact, and your next opportunity

‚Ä¶you‚Äôll find your people here.

________________________________________

 

**üì∏ Special guest: Lisa Barton Photography returns**

By popular demand, Lisa Barton Photography is back after the amazing response last time‚Äîshowcasing her work and connecting with creatives. If you‚Äôre thinking about fresh headshots, portfolio updates, or levelling up your professional image, this is a perfect chance to start that conversation in person.

________________________________________

 

**Event details**

üóìÔ∏è Sunday 22 February 2026

üïë 2:00 PM ‚Äì 6:30 PM

üìç HOME Mcr, 2 Tony Wilson Place, Manchester, M15 4FN

 

üéüÔ∏è Tickets are live now (and these events get busy‚Äîdon‚Äôt leave it late):

[https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1925427307909](https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1925427307909)

________________________________________

 

**ü§ù Bring the energy. Leave with connections.**

 

If you‚Äôre serious about film, you already know: your next opportunity often comes from who you meet and who remembers you.

 

Share this with actors, filmmakers and crew you know‚Äîlet‚Äôs fill the room with people who actually make things happen. üé•‚ú®

# [CASTING CALL] NON-UNION BG FOR VERTICAL MICRODRAMA

Looking for background performer with basketball experience for the following dates:

**SHOOTING DATES: **JAN 29, 31, FEB 1-3

**LOCATION: **Abbotsford, North Vancouver and Squamish (fuel compensation available for travel to Abbotsford and Squamish)

*Must have reliable vehicle

* Non-Union
* POC encouraged
* Age 19-25
* 5'10" to 6'1"
* Must have their own basketball shoes
* Intermediate/advanced basketball skill set

Pay rate: $144.80/8hr, OT applied thereafter.

If interested, please email: **casting@yymediaco.com**, using "**The Comeback Play - Basketball Player**" in the subject line. In the message, please include your **height, availability, a brief description of your basketball experience, and agency** (if applicable). As well as **a headshot**. 

Thank you in advance!

We‚Äôre casting **2 on-camera performers** to play a **couple arriving at a vacation home** for a lifestyle brand video shoot in **Squamish, BC**.

* Rate: **$400 flat** per person
* Union status: **Non-union**
* Usage: **Brand marketing** (web + social)

Roles (2 Talent)

**Couple (Ages 35‚Äì55)**

SONGS FROM LIFE with Stefanie Rummel  @adlfringe & @newcastlefringe Fringe 
Let the melodies carry you... the stories transform you.

AUSTRALIAN PREMIERE: 
https://adelaidefringe.com.au/fringetix/songs-from-life-af2026

Award-winning singer Stefanie Rummel takes you on a captivating musical journey ‚Äî from the caf√©s of Paris to the cabarets of Berlin, and the clubs of Manhattan. 
Featuring songs in the style of Piaf, Weill, Sondheim, and her own original works.
Through stories and songs, Stefanie ignites longing, laughter, and love ‚Äî in a show that touches hearts and minds.
Seven chansons were written by Stefanie Rummel (lyrics & music). They were arranged and produced in collaboration with Tom Schl√ºter (pianist & music producer).
Praised as ‚Äúsoul-touching‚Äù and ‚Äúbrilliant showmanship‚Äù, Stefanie Rummel has enchanted audiences across the US, UK, Europe, and Australia.
‚ÄúYou beautifully blended your life experiences and stories into a creative music journey with such thoughtful themes. Your insights and heartfelt messages truly moved me and continue to echo in my heart long after the show.‚Äù

A sparkling celebration of life, music, and connection ‚Äî cabaret at its most heartfelt.

üé∏ Durch eine Einladung in Instagram, durch den Musiker und Schauspieler Florian Thunemann, bin ich gestern auf dieses kleine Kultur-Universum gesto√üen: 

üïäÔ∏è ‚ÄûLong Erich & Friends‚Äú trifft ‚ÄûLohse Saiten‚Äú, von Blues, Rock und Folk bis Gypsy Swing. 

ü§ç Ich habe Florian zwei Fotos gemacht und heute am PC daraus ein kleines Video geformt, Gitarrenmusik darunter, Herz dar√ºber. 

üé∏ Dabei ist mir dieser Vers in den Kopf gekommen und ich lasse ihn genau so stehen: 

üïäÔ∏è "So wie Du Bilder 
zu Geschichten formst, 
formt der Groove Dich 
zu einem Menschen, 
der wieder im Takt atmet." 

ü§ç Livemusik ist mehr als Unterhaltung, sie ist ein friedlicher Treffpunkt f√ºr K√∂rper, Geist und Seele. Wenn Kultur √ºberall genug Raum bekommt, wird die Welt leiser im Hass und lauter im Verstehen, dann geben wir nicht denen Macht, die vom Krieg leben, sondern denen, die vom Miteinander erz√§hlen. 

ü§çüé∏üïäÔ∏è Unterst√ºtze Clubs, B√ºhnen, Stra√üenmusik, Prober√§ume, kleine Events, genau dort f√§ngt Frieden an, im echten Klang, in echten Blicken, in echter N√§he. 

ü§çüé∏üïäÔ∏è Bilder und Text @christian_weisse_digi_content

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äî VIDEO SUBMISSION REQUIRED

We‚Äôre casting 10 actors for a 1-minute product promo video and are looking for bilingual talent.

üìç Location: DTLA (studio)
üí∞ Pay: $600
üìÖ Shoot Date: Feb 3 (up to 5 hrs, ~2 hrs expected)
üëï Wardrobe Fitting: Jan 30 (30 min)
üì∫ Usage: Internet + events (copyright buyout)

üé≠ WHO WE‚ÄôRE LOOKING FOR

‚úîÔ∏è Any gender
‚úîÔ∏è Ages 14‚Äì90
‚úîÔ∏è Fluent in English + ONE of the following languages:
Spanish, French, German, Japanese, Portuguese, Italian, Dutch, Hindi, Russian

üé• AUDITION REQUIREMENT (MANDATORY)

Please submit a self-tape video of you reading the script below in English AND in your second language.

‚ö†Ô∏è Incomplete submissions will not be considered.

Script (must be read in full, twice):

‚ÄúI get nervous every time I speak, especially when I can‚Äôt see the person on the other end. Without faces or gestures, words have to carry more weight‚Äîand sometimes they fall short. I‚Äôm working every day to bridge that gap. What I hope for isn‚Äôt special treatment; I just hope one day I can be understood for my ideas, for my thinking, and not my accent or where I come from. And I hope that day is today.‚Äù

üì© HOW TO SUBMIT

Email your video self-tape to:
üìß casting@verkada.com

Please include:

Name

Age

Languages spoken

Confirmation of availability for Jan 30 & Feb 3

üé¨ We‚Äôre casting 10 actors ‚Äî excited to see your tapes!

items.text:
üé¨ **CALLING CAMERA OPS & SCRIPT SUPERVISORS (LA)**

*3-Day Short Film | Skill Exchange Opportunity*

****1ST COME 1ST SERVE ****

We‚Äôre currently crewing up for a **3-day short film production** and are looking to connect with a few aligned creatives who want to collaborate, build, and create something meaningful together.

**Positions we‚Äôre seeking:**

‚Ä¢ Camera Operator familiar with **Sony & Blackmagic** systems

‚Ä¢ **Script Supervisor**

This project is **unpaid**, but  we‚Äôre offering a **creative exchange** for those who are interested.

‚ú® **What you receive:**

If you have a **concept, visual, or short idea (up to 10 minutes)** you‚Äôve been wanting to bring to life, you‚Äôll receive **full production support** from our collective on your piece (crew, structure, guidance, execution) in exchange for your support on this film.

This is ideal for creatives who:

‚Ä¢ Want real on-set experience with an intentional team

‚Ä¢ Have a short visual idea they‚Äôve been sitting on

‚Ä¢ Value collaboration over transactional gigs

‚Ä¢ Are interested in long-term creative relationships

üìç **Location:** Los Angeles

üìÜ **Shoot:** 3 days (dates shared upon connection)

If this resonates, comment below or DM with:

1. Your role (Cam Op or Script Supervisor)
2. Gear familiarity (if applicable)
3. A brief note on the visual you‚Äôd want support on

ich w√ºrde gerne zwei Workshop-Angebote mit Euch teilen, die wirklich absolut klasse sind:

sharedPost.text:
North Texas Film Alliance is excited to announce our new strategic partnership and collaboration with Stage 32.
Stage 32 is a global online platform and social network for film, television, and theater creatives, connecting writers, actors, directors, producers, and other professionals to network, learn, and find opportunities, featuring educational webinars, script services, job boards, and a supportive community to democratize the entertainment industry. It provides access to industry executives, educational content, and a marketplace for projects, helping members develop skills and advance careers.

To kick off our new partnership, NTFA will partner with Stage 32 to host a complimentary one hour virtual webinar on Wednesday, January 28th at 6:00 CST showcasing the power of Stage 32‚Äôs educational and collaborative platform, connecting you with industry professionals and opportunities.
In the webinar, you‚Äôll learn about the benefits of Stage 32 Certification and how your certification will lead to more opportunities with NTFA.

Attendees will receive a 50% off coupon for all Stage 32 Certification Courses.

#Filmmakers #texas #stage32 #webinar #filmmaking

items.text:
First short-film showreel
Today I set myself the challenge of writing, recordings and editing my own short film to showcase as part of my showreel for my acting. 

With no experience in acting, except a law degree,ife experience, observation and emotional intelligence. I out forward a project that I set out and achieved. 

I can‚Äôt express enough how fun this was, despite not living the best life circumstances in my family house. I was able to find escape through my art. 

This was my first short film, I didnt film many takes, and I didn‚Äôt look back at any footage (which I should have) but I wanted to get the project finished through the chaos of what was going on around me and have something solid, whether professional or not, to showcase my ability. 

Jake Nova ‚ù§Ô∏è

items.summary:
First short-film showreel
Today I set myself the challenge of writing, recordings and editing my own short film to showcase as part of my showreel for my acting. 

With no experience in acting, except a law degree,ife experience, observation and emotional intelligence. I out forward a project that I set out and achieved. 

I can‚Äôt express enough how fun this was, despite not living the best life circumstances in my family house. I was able to find escape through my art. 

This was my first short film, I didnt film many takes, and I didn‚Äôt look back at any footage (which I should have) but I wanted to get the project finished through the chaos of what was going on around me and have something solid, whether professional or not, to showcase my ability. 

Jake Nova ‚ù§Ô∏è
items.title: First short-film showreel

Casting for leading Man/Leading Lady young adult early to mid-20's.
I'm shooting another short vertical demo for two days between now and February 8 (dates TBA) and am looking for two non-union actors with comedic acting chops, to play out the dialogue in this romantic comedy (a few scenes).

Shooting will be in downtown and East Vancouver, there will be a rehearsal day after actors are off-book and then we shoot.

This is a demo, voluntary, for actors reel and directing sample.

If interested, please email me your photo, resume and availability to castingproject604@gmail.com.

**CASTING CALL - Non-union **

Looking for Slavic/Eastern European looking actors for small, non-speaking roles in short film, During Winter, I Thought of My Father, a Russian language short film by Daniil Vasilyev. 

**ACTORS DO NOT NEED TO SPEAK RUSSIAN AS THE ROLES ARE NON-SPEAKING. **

**Main Shoot Dates: Feb 14th-16th, 2026 **

**Descriptions: **

**Young Russian Man, early 20s: **Need him available for a day in the week leading up to Feb 14th for a photoshoot. 
Specific date TBD, but we are flexible and willing to work with actor's schedule. 

**Older Russian Woman, 50s-60s: **Needed for photoshoot Feb 16th. 

**Older Russian Man, 40s-60s: **Needed for filming Feb 14th, 15th, photoshoot on the 16th. Non-speaking role, will be playing main character's father. 

**Compensation: **IMDb credit, post-film credit, food provided as well as transport if required**. **

**Location: **Greater Vancouver Area 

**If interested, please send an email to ****duringwinter26@gmail.com ****with any headshots or good pictures of yourself, your reel (if you have one), and stats (height, eye colour, etc). **

** **

Suche f√ºr ein Musikvideo noch eine Mitspielerin.
 
Gedreht wird zu einem etwas rockigeren Song der gut auf die breite Masse passt. 
Thema ist ‚ÄúLippenstift‚Äù Hei√üt - Du bist die sch√∂nste und darfst dich sch√∂n aufbrezeln. 
Ich Idiot stehe daneben und trage deine T√ºten und gebe dir immer eine bestfriend Meinung. 
 
Im Laufe des Songs ziehe ich das ganze aber mehr und mehr ins l√§cherliche und bring dich zum verzweifeln. 
 
Gedreht werden soll das ganze in einem Supermarkt/Drogerie einem Club oder √§hnlichen und einem Modehaus 
( Szenen beim einkaufen und nat√ºrlich vor dem Lippenstift Regal und vor dem Club ) 
Das Video soll etwas ironisch und spa√üig gestaltet werden, Konfetti schie√üen, Feenstaub werfen etc. Am Ende darfst du mir sogar zeigen wie ich selber fachlich Lippenstift auftrage. 
 
Du musst kein Profi sein 
bestenfalls im Alter von 18 ‚Äì 26 
jugendlicher Stil , schlank und am besten blond oder braunhaarig. 
 
Du solltest arrogant und eingebildet schauen k√∂nnen und etwas gestikulieren. 
Viel mehr ist nicht n√∂tig. 
Und dir das nat√ºrlich zutrauen zu drehen auch wenn es Zuschauer gibt. 
 
Drehort: L√ºneburger Umkreis 
Datum folgt wenn die Locations zugesagt haben. 
Vorweg kann nat√ºrlich ein pers√∂nliches treffen stattfinden um alles durchzukaspern. 
 
Als Dankesch√∂n bekommst du einen Gutschein deiner Wahl im Wert von 50‚Ç¨ ein Fotoshooting f√ºrs Coverbild des Songs und den gekauften Lippenstift hahahah. 
Alle entstandenen Aufnahmen/Bilder darfst du nat√ºrlich auch f√ºr eigene Zwecke verwenden.

Auf Wunsch kann ich dir auch schon ein paar Songausschnitte zeigen :)

items.text:
üé¨üéûÔ∏èCasting call for student short film: ‚ÄòDon‚Äôt Forget the Butter‚Äô  

We are casting for a short film (7-9 minutes) for our second year project at Greenwich University.

Synopsis:

A man sets out to complete the next task on a bucket list: find the best toast topping. As the story unfolds, it is revealed that the bucket list belonged to his late girlfriend, who passed suddenly and unexpectedly. Completing the list becomes his way of honouring her memory and processing his grief.

Filming: East London, w/c 23rd February - w/c 2nd March (exact date TBC)

Important: Please ensure you are able to travel to East London (end of the district line) prior to expressing your interest. 

If you are interested in character 3 - you will need to be able to travel to Greenwich instead of East London, dates TBC.

As this is a student production, the roles are unpaid. However, travel and expenses and food will be provided. This film will be used within our portfolios - you are welcome to add this to your own portfolio and/or showreels. 

If you are interested or would like to hear more, please email the following to: [lh3568v@gre.ac.uk](mailto:lh3568v@gre.ac.uk) 
* Which character you are applying for
* Headshot and CV
* Availability

CASTING CALL!!! (Princess Tiana)
Asking on behalf of a 6 year old!!

We have exhausted all of the character party supplies businesses, what we are looking for is someone could could play TIANA (DISNEY PRINCESS) from PRINCESS AND THE FROG for about an hour for a little girl‚Äôs birthday party in Cwmbran, South Wales. The going rate for this type of work and travel time and expenses would be paid. Party food included ü§£. 

Obviously as the 6 year old still thinks it would be the ‚Äòreal‚Äô Tiana we are seeking someone who could embody her in looks and confidence, and provide a southern American accent like in the movie. Good with kids helps! 

Please share and tag, ask your friends! FYI party companies charge about ¬£100 for the hour and we were willing to pay them this then the travel costs and time on top. Great for a theatre student or something to add to a portfolio. 

Thanks in advance!

items.text:
üé∏ Durch eine Einladung in Instagram, durch den Musiker und Schauspieler Florian Thunemann, bin ich gestern auf dieses kleine Kultur-Universum gesto√üen: 

üïäÔ∏è ‚ÄûLong Erich & Friends‚Äú trifft ‚ÄûLohse Saiten‚Äú, von Blues, Rock und Folk bis Gypsy Swing. 

ü§ç Ich habe Florian zwei Fotos gemacht und heute am PC daraus ein kleines Video geformt, Gitarrenmusik darunter, Herz dar√ºber. 

üé∏ Dabei ist mir dieser Vers in den Kopf gekommen und ich lasse ihn genau so stehen: 

üïäÔ∏è "So wie Du Bilder 
zu Geschichten formst, 
formt der Groove Dich 
zu einem Menschen, 
der wieder im Takt atmet." 

ü§ç Livemusik ist mehr als Unterhaltung, sie ist ein friedlicher Treffpunkt f√ºr K√∂rper, Geist und Seele. Wenn Kultur √ºberall genug Raum bekommt, wird die Welt leiser im Hass und lauter im Verstehen, dann geben wir nicht denen Macht, die vom Krieg leben, sondern denen, die vom Miteinander erz√§hlen. 

ü§çüé∏üïäÔ∏è Unterst√ºtze Clubs, B√ºhnen, Stra√üenmusik, Prober√§ume, kleine Events, genau dort f√§ngt Frieden an, im echten Klang, in echten Blicken, in echter N√§he. 

ü§çüé∏üïäÔ∏è Bilder und Text @christian_weisse_digi_content 

#LongErichAndFriends #LohseSaiten #FlorianThunemann #Wundertuete #Koeln

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì LIVERPOOL ACTORS WANTED 

We're casting for "They Were All Some Mothers' Sons" ‚Äì a powerful true story returning to the stage at Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot in May 2026.

This sell-out production tells the remarkable true story of German POWs detained in Huyton during WWII who fell in love with local women and chose to stay, becoming part of our community. 

Previously performed to packed houses in Liverpool and Germany.

Roles available:

 Jean ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Eleanor ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Marjorie ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Joey ‚Äì Young British RAF pilot, male, playing age 18-24

 Mother ‚Äì female, playing age 40+

 Father ‚Äì male, playing age 40+

Key dates:

 Auditions: First week of February

 Rehearsals: Mid-March to show

 Performances: 1st, 2nd May 2026 (possible 3rd date)

 Venue: Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot

This is a paid role (profit share)

This is Prescot's own heritage story‚Äîtold in the heart of Knowsley, where it all happened over 80 years ago. We're looking for passionate local talent to bring this living history to life.

To apply: Send your CV and headshot to howl.michael1963@yahoo.co.uk specifying which role and which production you want to audition for.

Please prepare a 2-minute monologue of your choice for audition.

We're casting for "They Were All Some Mothers' Sons" ‚Äì a powerful true story returning to the stage at Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot in May 2026.

This sell-out production tells the remarkable true story of German POWs detained in Huyton during WWII who fell in love with local women and chose to stay, becoming part of our community. 

Previously performed to packed houses in Liverpool and Germany.

items.text:
CASTING CALL - ASAP

25/01/25

The Party No One Wanted (Short Film)

**A dark comedy about grief and family relationships.**

Robbie and Mary have to get through an excruciating memorial that has a DJ, karaoke and a pregnancy announcement / gender reveal planned by their half sister Lisa.

* **Shooting 6th - 9th March in TW19**
* Auditions in Elephant and Castle within the next few weeks
* **Travel Expenses Paid**
* Student film hoping to go to Film festivals
* **Robbie **(28-38yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Emotionally withdrawn but has a kind heart, he's holding it together for Mary and his Dad
* **Steve** (57-70yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Mary, Robbie and Lisa‚Äôs dad doesn‚Äôt get involved in the arguing he‚Äôs still devastated by the loss of his wife but insists he‚Äôs fine.
* **Lisa** (39-47yrs) Southern English Accent
   * Self centred and definitely doesn‚Äôt know whats appropriate at a memorial. 
* **Natalie** (49-65yrs)
   * A close family friend who has taken on a bit of a motherly role to everyone, kind and soft spoken.
* **Bill** (50-65yrs) 
   * The drunk best friend of steve who has awful timing for his awkward comments. Very funny character

**Character Bios: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ipHj1IfKbJSUPp5iRRgmOc37l-Y1RZsP-QQfkD3fyGY/edit?usp=sharing)** **

**Director‚Äôs Statement: **[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1j7Tns7vph04wJiUQMCFhf1RKu4n00us00ARUfFXqBdI/edit?usp=sharing) 

Email: [mhmollie0303@icloud.com](mailto:mhmollie0303@icloud.com) for further details

CASTING CALL ‚Äì LIVERPOOL ACTORS WANTED 

We're casting for "They Were All Some Mothers' Sons" ‚Äì a powerful true story returning to the stage at Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot in May 2026.

This sell-out production tells the remarkable true story of German POWs detained in Huyton during WWII who fell in love with local women and chose to stay, becoming part of our community. 

Previously performed to packed houses in Liverpool and Germany.

Roles available:

 Jean ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Eleanor ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Marjorie ‚Äì female, playing age 18-25

 Joey ‚Äì Young British RAF pilot, male, playing age 18-24

 Mother ‚Äì female, playing age 40+

 Father ‚Äì male, playing age 40+

Key dates:

 Auditions: First week of February

 Rehearsals: Mid-March to show

 Performances: 1st, 2nd May 2026 (possible 3rd date)

 Venue: Shakespeare North Playhouse, Prescot

This is a paid role (profit share)

This is Prescot's own heritage story‚Äîtold in the heart of Knowsley, where it all happened over 80 years ago. We're looking for passionate local talent to bring this living history to life.

To apply: Send your CV and headshot to howl.michael1963@yahoo.co.uk specifying which role and which production you want to audition for.

Please prepare a 2-minute monologue of your choice for audition.

items.text:
First short-film showreel
Today I set myself the challenge of writing, recordings and editing my own short film to showcase as part of my showreel for my acting. 

With no experience in acting, except a law degree,ife experience, observation and emotional intelligence. I out forward a project that I set out and achieved. 

I can‚Äôt express enough how fun this was, despite not living the best life circumstances in my family house. I was able to find escape through my art. 

This was my first short film, I didnt film many takes, and I didn‚Äôt look back at any footage (which I should have) but I wanted to get the project finished through the chaos of what was going on around me and have something solid, whether professional or not, to showcase my ability. 

Jake Nova ‚ù§Ô∏è

CASTING CALL - small indie film shooting in Colorado Springs on January 30. There are 2 scenes shooting that day. 
1. Coffee Shop: 12 people, portraying patrons, students, etc., dressed in comfortable clothes, 1p-5p.
2. Hospital: 3 people, portraying EMS personnel, dressed in scrubs, 6p-9p.

Rate: IMDB credit, crafty available, footage upon completion

Production Company: Legacy Landmarks Studio, Golden Hour Grid

Title: The Last Frame

Logline: A military veteran finds happiness and purpose after meeting the woman who changes his life - but after a sudden accident and one irreversible mistake, their love collapses into devastating consequences. 

Genre: Drama

Run Time: 10 minutes

Location: Colorado Springs, Colorado

Distribution: YouTube, February 11, 2026

TO SUBMIT: Email [legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com](mailto:legacylandmarksstudio@gmail.com) ; Subject: TLF Casting; Include: Headshot, Resume, Reel (if available), Role you are submitting for, Availability for 1/30/2026.

Note: In exchange for offering your services as an actor, our production team would like to offer a 10 second footage compilation of your individual performance on this project for your demo reel. Please submit by January 26, 2026. Thank you!

CASTING CALL - Short Dark Comedy/Noir
‚Ä¢ Title: "Murder, No Rush"

‚Ä¢ Type: Short

‚Ä¢ Location: Boulder, CO, Denver, CO

‚Ä¢ Compensation: $25/day (negotiable), lunch provided

‚Ä¢ Shooting Dates: Sunday, January 25th & Sunday, February 1st

SYNOPSIS

Vivian, a vain housewife, conspires to kill her wealthy husband, Benny, by hiring a hitman- but unbeknownst to her, the cops know exactly what she's up to.

ROLES:

‚Ä¢ Benny D'Angelo: Male, 23-35
Vivian's husband. A well-off businessman who fell in love easily, only to now find that his wife might have married him just for the money.

‚Ä¢ Officer K: Male, 30+
A no-nonsense cop with a keen attention to detail. He arrives on the scene of an apparent drug bust, only to discover there may be something much more sinister at hand.
(Only needed on 1/25)

TO SUBMIT:

‚Ä¢ A headshot OR previous work OR request sides, record an audition (please submit by Friday, January 23)

‚Ä¢ Subject Line: "[Your Name] - Murder, No Rush"

If you're interested, please feel free to DM me directly here or email AydanMetsch@gmail.com. Script available upon request!

items.text:
CASTING CALL - Short Dark Comedy/Noir
‚Ä¢ Title: "Murder, No Rush"
‚Ä¢ Type: Short
‚Ä¢ Location: Boulder, CO
‚Ä¢ Compensation: $50 (negotiable), lunch provided
‚Ä¢ Time Commitment: 2 half-days (3-5 hours)

SYNOPSIS
Vivian, a vain housewife, conspires to kill her wealthy husband by hiring a hitman- but unbeknownst to her, the cops know exactly what she's up to.

ROLES:

‚Ä¢ The Contractor: Male, 28-45+
A contract killer. Stoic, calculating, and cold-blooded; or at least that how he seems. Unknown to his client, he is secretly working for the police, undercover as a hitman.

‚Ä¢ Detective Moss: Female, 30s+
An interrogator who knows how to get a confession without raising her voice. But she doesn't just want to prove guilt: she wants to know why.

TO SUBMIT:
‚Ä¢ A headshot OR previous work OR request sides, record an audition.
‚Ä¢ Subject Line: "[Your Name] - Murder, No Rush" 

If you're interested, please feel free to DM me directly here or email AydanMetsch@gmail.com. Script available upon request!
